				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Warrior CC?<a name="54744"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 2 04 9:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I play a 54 warrior off and on so I know where the warrior is coming from. But frankly, with just Bellow, a warrior is hard pressed to keep two mobs in line if not given a second or two to establish some aggro.
<br />

<br />
When I MA, I'd personally much rather the adds were mezzed(maybe thats the bard side of me speaking?). 
<br />

<br />
I did an adventure last night when the bard was CC and I was MA. When he'd pull adds I'd let him mezz them. Occasionally, one add flies loose and heads for the shaman. When I see it, I toggle target, tap my bellow button and then taunt. I generally won't melee in case the bard cycles through the mezz again. Hopefully the mob I was tanking previously hasnt forgotten about me.
<br />

<br />
Don't fret the details so much, you'll live longer. You have to just let the group do what they find works, if that means no mezzing, then so be it. If the warrior cant handle the double tanking the cleric will be the one to set him straight. You have plenty to do anyway, if not mezzing.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
