			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Warrior CC?<a name="54833"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 2 04 6:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Aye, I wasn't worried or concerned, just trying to lift my game a little.  I'm happy to do what works in any situation -- that kind of flexibility is part of being a bard, I think -- but it's more difficult to agree that it's the best thing to do.
<br />

<br />
I'm an efficiency-freak, I admit it!
<br />

<br />
As such, I did a little back-of-the-envelope calculation.  Assume 30% slow, 40% haste and mez were my only songs, and that my timing and twisting were perfect, as was the timing and taunting of the tank.  Then two mobs will do 1.5 times the damage if I slow the add rather than mez it.
<br />

<br />
I guess that it's right that the cleric will sing out if things aren't going well, however.  I'm just used to filling in the holes on pick-up adventures, and that makes me skeptical of other people's abilities until I see what they can do.  No doubt they are all thinking exactly the same things...!
<br />

<br />
